reviews.review_text: Everything is exactly pitch perfect. Thanks Charlie for perfectly pitched upgrade.  Great bass and balance. You are the soundboard "Gold Standard" and a Deadicated Hero.  Still amazed we have the archive and the energy that goes into being exactly pitch perfect.  Hopefully Jerry is smiling for you  as well!

Now Perfect! For years this show has been available for listening, but the longest ever version of 'Here Comes Sunshine' was ruined by the last 25 seconds dissolving into a very rough audience recording. Now, from somewhere, Charlie Miller has dug up a complete version. Not only that, he has improved the entire show with a better, cleaner sound and pitch correction, making this one of the best shows in a year filled with best shows. 

However, this concert will never be released. First some highlights were available among the old 'nugs dot net' site that offered about two dozen or more shows for free downloads in their SBD versions. Then some more songs became available as filler on one of the Road Trips 'bonus disc' releases. So, since at the time, no known complete version of this Here Comes Sunshine was available for the archives, it was not among the songs released. Now here it is: why can't this great version of a great song be released on one of the '30 Days of Dead' offerings? Or, as filler on one of the Dave's Picks releases? Please, please, please!

Glorious I'm probably gonna listen to this one a couple times.
Thanks Charlie
